1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,011
Remember the complete method in three lines.

2
00:00:02,961 --> 00:00:07,990
If one augmented model call can solve the task, do not build a workflow first.

3
00:00:07,990 --> 00:00:13,134
If you can draw the execution path in advance, do not build an autonomous agent first.

4
00:00:13,134 --> 00:00:21,192
When you truly need an agent, protect it with environmental feedback, stopping conditions, permissions, and reliable tool interfaces.

5
00:00:21,192 --> 00:00:30,038
The Agent Architecture Decision Ladder is simple: one augmented call, then a controlled workflow, then runtime orchestration, and only then full autonomy.

6
00:00:30,038 --> 00:00:36,221
Keep each upgrade only when completion rate, cost, latency, or human effort measurably improves.

7
00:00:36,221 --> 00:00:39,413
Mature agent systems do not maximize freedom.

8
00:00:39,413 --> 00:00:42,432
They make every layer of freedom earn its place.

9
00:00:42,432 --> 00:00:51,750
Follow Tiny Agent to keep turning fast-moving AI and agent ideas into practical ways to choose tasks, delegate work, verify results, and control risk.
